<glossary>
<definition id="fs-id1167583525361">
<term>electric dipole</term>
<meaning id="fs-id1167583525366">system of two equal but opposite charges a fixed distance apart</meaning>
</definition>
<definition id="fs-id1167583525371">
<term>electric dipole moment</term>
<meaning id="fs-id1167583525376">quantity defined as <m:math><m:mrow><m:mstyle mathvariant="bold" mathsize="normal"><m:mover accent="true"><m:mtext>p</m:mtext><m:mo stretchy="false">→</m:mo></m:mover></m:mstyle><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mi>q</m:mi><m:mstyle mathvariant="bold" mathsize="normal"><m:mover accent="true"><m:mtext>d</m:mtext><m:mo stretchy="false">→</m:mo></m:mover></m:mstyle></m:mrow></m:math> for all dipoles, where the vector points from the negative to positive charge</meaning>
</definition>
</glossary>

